.TH $file-size-prompt 5
.XI $file-size-prompt - "Large file size warning prompt"
.SH NAME
$file-size-prompt \- Large file size warning prompt
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB$file-size-prompt\fR "\fIinteger\fR"; Default is "\fC1024\fR"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sets the size, in megabytes, to trigger a warning prompt before  loading a file. Any attempt to load a file this size
or larger will result in a "\fCFile <name> is #MB, continue  ?\fR", entering  '\fBN\fR' or aborting will stop the file
loading processes resulting in an empty buffer.
.PP
The default value is 1024MB, i.e. 1 gigabyte.
